{
  "number": 1843,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1843",
  "title": "Search For Facet Values: SearchBox translations",
  "body": "Use Case: I want to change the placeholder of the SearchBox used for SFFV in the RefinementList/Menu\r\n\r\n```js\r\n<RefinementList attributeName=\"category\" searchForFacetValues\r\n                    translations={{placeholder: 'Search for products'}}/>\r\n```\r\n\r\nBehavior: Nothing happen\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThis is happening because the `translate` function we built for the RefinementList/Menu is overridden by the one built for the `<SearchBox/>`.\r\n\r\nI see two ways for fixing this:\r\n\r\n- We do not override the first translate function built. It means that if a component A use a component B, then every translations should already have been taken care of by the component A. \r\n\r\n- We forward the `translations` props to every widgets (it's not the case today, we use this props to build the `translate` props, but we do not forward the `translations`object). It means that if a component A uses a component B, then he will need to forward the `translations` keys props to the component B, in order for it to build the correct `translate` function. \r\n\r\nIn either case, we need to add the `<SearchBox/>` translations propTypes to the `<RefinementList/>/<Menu/>`.\r\n",
